name: Tavë Kosi
description: A traditional Albanian dish of baked lamb and rice, topped with a yogurt and egg mixture.

name: Bakllasarem
description: A sweet pastry filled with a mixture of walnuts, sugar, and cinnamon, similar to baklava.

name: Fërgesë
description: A hearty dish of peppers, tomatoes, and cottage cheese, often served as a warm side dish or main course.

name: Speca të mbushur
description: Bell peppers stuffed with rice, herbs, and seafood, baked until tender.

name: Byrek me Spinaq
description: A savory pie made with phyllo dough, filled with spinach and feta cheese.

name: Jani me fasule
description: A traditional bean stew slowly cooked with onions, tomatoes, and spices.

name: Shëndetli
description: A walnut cake soaked in syrup, often served during special occasions and holidays.

name: Qifqi
description: Rice balls seasoned with mint and fried until crispy, a popular dish from Gjirokastër.

name: Përime në zgare
description: A variety of grilled vegetables, typically seasoned with olive oil, salt, and herbs.

name: Mish me midhje
description: A seafood dish featuring sautéed mussels with garlic, wine, and fresh herbs, often served over pasta or with crusty bread.

name: Cheeseburger
description: A classic American cheeseburger with a juicy beef patty, topped with cheddar cheese, lettuce, tomato, onions, and pickles, served on a toasted bun.

name: Apple Pie
description: A traditional American dessert, this apple pie features a flaky pastry crust filled with sweet and spicy cinnamon apple filling.

name: Fried Chicken
description: Crispy fried chicken, seasoned with a blend of spices and fried to a perfect golden brown.

name: Macaroni and Cheese
description: A creamy, cheesy macaroni and cheese dish, baked until bubbly and golden.

name: Barbecue Ribs
description: Slow-cooked pork ribs slathered in barbecue sauce, grilled until tender and caramelized.

name: Pancakes
description: Fluffy American pancakes, served hot with butter and maple syrup.

name: Chocolate Chip Cookies
description: Classic soft and chewy chocolate chip cookies, loaded with chocolate chips and baked to perfection.

name: BLT Sandwich
description: A simple but delicious sandwich with bacon, lettuce, and tomato, served on toasted bread with mayonnaise.

name: Clam Chowder
description: A creamy New England clam chowder, rich with clams, potatoes, onions, and celery, thickened with cream and served with oyster crackers.

name: Brownies
description: Rich, fudgy chocolate brownies with a moist center and crispy edges, filled with chunks of chocolate.

name: Shopska Salata
description: A traditional Bulgarian salad made from tomatoes, cucumbers, onions, and topped with a generous amount of sirene cheese.

name: Kavarma
description: A hearty Bulgarian stew made with meat (typically pork or chicken), onions, mushrooms, and peppers, seasoned with paprika and herbs.

name: Banitsa
description: A traditional Bulgarian pastry made from layers of phyllo dough filled with eggs and cheese.

name: Mekitsa
description: A traditional Bulgarian breakfast, mekitsa is a deep-fried dough pastry, served with powdered sugar, honey, or jam.

name: Musaka
description: Bulgarian style moussaka is a baked dish of potatoes, minced meat, and a topping of yogurt and eggs, similar to the Greek version but without eggplant.

name: Tarator
description: A cold yogurt soup popular in the summer, made with cucumbers, garlic, dill, and walnuts.

name: Kadaif
description: A dessert of shredded phyllo dough, baked with nuts and saturated with syrup.

name: Bulgarian Cheese Toast
description: A quick and satisfying breakfast item made with bread, Bulgarian cheese, and often topped with a fried egg.

name: Garash Cake
description: A rich chocolate cake made with layers of walnut sponge cake and dark chocolate ganache, named after the Hungarian pastry chef Garash.

name: Sarmi
description: Traditional Bulgarian stuffed cabbage rolls filled with a mix of minced meats, rice, and herbs, cooked in a tomato-based sauce.

name: Beef Stroganoff
description: A classic rich and creamy Russian dish featuring sautéed pieces of beef served in a sauce with smetana (sour cream).

name: Medovik
description: A popular Russian honey cake featuring several thin layers of cake filled with sweetened sour cream.

name: Borscht
description: A hearty beet soup traditionally served hot or cold with a dollop of sour cream.

name: Pelmeni
description: Traditional Russian dumplings filled with minced meat and wrapped in a thin dough, served with butter or sour cream.

name: Syrniki
description: Sweet cheese pancakes made from tvorog (cottage cheese), typically served with sour cream or jam.

name: Kasha
description: A staple of Russian cuisine, kasha refers to any grain cooked in water or milk, often served as a side dish.

name: Pryaniki
description: Traditional Russian honey bread cookies spiced with ginger and cloves, often glazed with sugar icing.

name: Zefir
description: A type of soft confectionery made by whipping fruit and berry purée with sugar and egg whites, similar to marshmallows.

name: Olivier Salad
description: Also known as Russian Salad, this dish is a combination of diced potatoes, vegetables, eggs, and meat dressed with mayonnaise.

name: Shchi
description: A traditional Russian soup made with cabbage, meat, and various vegetables, known for its hearty and comforting qualities.
